# README
Library providing some helper functionalities for Splunk Cloud TAs

# Development
## Dependencies
To install all dependencies (including dev) use the following command:
```
poetry install
```

## Commit Hooks
To enable `pre-commit` hooks (needs to be done only once per env) run:
```
pre-commit install
```

## Pull Requests
General guidelines:
- Follow conventional commits naming convention for both commits and pull request titles
- Squash your commits while merging - it's always nice to have a clean commit history. You can do it either with `Squash and merge` GitHub functionality or manually using `git rebase -i`

## Releases
To create a new release tag for this library execute the following commands:

```
bump-my-version <part>    # part - `patch`, `minor` or `major`

git push
git push --tags
```

# Next Steps
- automate release tag creation
- add CI/CD

